			<div class="content" id="post-content-4093954">
									

<p>It's an author page. Once folks have contributed a modest amount of things to the wiki, creating an author page is a useful way for readers to see more of their work if interested in doing so. I'm just using a cheeky format.</p>
<p>This would be more clear if my images were showing up yet since one of them is a very recent selfie -_-;;</p>
<p><strong>Edit:</strong> Oh, also! &quot;Mise en place&quot; is a culinary term which means &quot;how you prepare an ingredient for use in a recipe.&quot;</p>
<p>Since my general attitude towards the wiki is &quot;oo I want to smoosh all the pretty lore together and see what fun new monstrosities emerge&quot;, playing around with a food metaphor and punning on my username seemed apt.</p>

